Step 2:
Since $0abc$ is a square, $b$ is obtained by rotating $a$ by $90^\circ$ counterclockwise.  This means
\[b = ai = (p + qi)i = -q + pi.\]Then $r = -q$ and $s = p,$ so $b = -q + pi.$

Step 3:
Also, $c$ is obtained by rotating $b$ by $90^\circ$ counterclockwise, so
\[c = bi = (-q + pi)i = -p - qi.\]Step 4:
Then
\begin{align*}
\frac{ac + b^2}{ab} &= \frac{(p + qi)(-p - qi) + (-q + pi)^2}{(p + qi)(-q + pi)} \\
&= \frac{-p^2 - 2pqi - q^2 i^2 + q^2 - 2pqi + p^2 i^2}{-pq + p^2 i - q^2 i + qi^2} \\
&= \frac{-p^2 - 2pqi + q^2 + q^2 - 2pqi - p^2}{-pq - q + (p^2 - q^2) i} \\
&= \frac{-2p^2 - 4pqi + 2q^2}{-(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q) + (p^2 - q^2) i} \\
&= \frac{2(q^2 - p^2 - 2pqi)}{-(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q) + (p^2 - q^2) i} \\
&= \frac{2(q^2 - p^2 - 2pqi)[-(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q) - (p^2 - q^2) i]}{[-(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q) + (p^2 - q^2) i][-(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q) - (p^2 - q^2) i]} \\
&= \frac{2[(q^2 - p^2)(-p^2 - q^2 - pq - q) + 2pq(p^2 - q^2)] + 2[(q^2 - p^2)(-p^2 + q^2) - 2pq(-p^2 - q^2 - pq - q)]i}{(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q)^2 + (p^2 - q^2)^2} \\
&= \frac{-4pq(p^2 + q^2) - 8p^2 qi}{(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q)^2 + (p^2 - q^2)^2} \\
&= \boxed{\frac{-4pq(p^2 + q^2) - 8p^2 qi}{(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q)^2 + (p^2 - q^2)^2}}.
\end{align*}
Final answer:
\boxed{\frac{-4pq(p^2 + q^2) - 8p^2 qi}{(p^2 + q^2 + pq + q)^2 + (p^2 - q^2)^2}}
